text.section:
A permit issued under this section may be revoked by the department when:
A false statement or misrepresentation of a material fact in the application, plans, or specifications led to the issuance of the permit;
The permit was issued in error;
The work detailed under the permit is not being performed in accordance with the application, plans, or specifications;
Work is not being performed in accordance with the code or conditions of the permit; or
The elevator contractor to whom the permit was issued fails or refuses to comply with a lawfully issued stop work order.
